On Mon, 06 Sep 1999 04:00:26 -0400, M. Berglund wrote:
> Is there anyone working on a debugger that is internal to the kernel for use 
> during a catastrophic failure, allowing for causing a panic(for testing) and 
> reading the registers during operation.  It seems like a good idea which has 
> been employed by the FreeBSD folk, and presumably the rest of that 
> crowd.  If anyone is working on it, I would like to help.
SGI is working on a kernel debugger called kdb, for details see
http://oss.sgi.com/projects/kdb/
